data.value:
Cleveland is a private clinic located in Hobhouse Township, Mutare in Zimbabwe. The clinic was founded by Doctor Moses Mullins in 2015 when an outbreak of malaria had hit Hobhouse. The majority of Hobhouse inhabitants (about 1500 people) usually visit this clinic since it is easily accessible and cheap in the area. The clinic has three branches, one in Mutare, the other in Harare and the last one in Bulawayo. There are three nurses, one doctor and two general workers at the clinic. The clinic is a minor branch of the other ones but neverthless, we do our best to satisfy you. The clinic provides cure or treatment for minor diseases since it is not fully developed yet. The clinic also offers guidance and counseling to HIV/AIDS patients.
